A boy has been missing for over 24 hours after he was last seen at Manchester Airport yesterday. Police have issued an urgent appeal for help finding the boy, named only as Kenny. He is described as being around 5ft fins tall, of slim build, and with short dark hair as seen in his passport photo. Officers have not released details of Kenny’s surname, hometown or age. It is believed he was wearing a black tracksuit and trainers at the time he went missing, and may still be in the same clothes. A spokesperson for Greater Manchester Police said: ‘Anyone who sees Kenny is asked to contact police. ‘Kenny has been reported missing and was last seen at Manchester Airport at around 9.30pm on June 23. ‘He is described as being as per this passport image and approximately 5ft 5ins tall and of a slim build. ‘Kenny is thought to be wearing a black tracksuit and black trainers.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.